{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Large system"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We now consider a larger system (e.g., 40 variables). MLE is intractable. Thus, we can just compare the performance of EM with HF and PLE.\n",
    "\n",
    "As usual, we import the necessary packages to the Jupyter notebook:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import emachine as EM"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###  Weak interactions and large sample size"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n_var = 40\n",
    "g = 0.5\n",
    "n_seq = 8000"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The synthetic data are generated by using `generate_seq`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "w_true,seqs = EM.generate_seq(n_var,n_seq,g=g)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We reconstruct the interactions from the sequences `seqs` (or `ops`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The optimal value of eps: 0.64\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Epsilon Machine (EM)\n",
    "ops = EM.operators(seqs)\n",
    "eps_list = np.linspace(0.5,0.8,16)\n",
    "E_eps = np.zeros(len(eps_list))\n",
    "w_eps = np.zeros((len(eps_list),ops.shape[1]))\n",
    "for i,eps in enumerate(eps_list):    \n",
    "    w_eps[i,:],E_eps[i] = EM.fit(ops,eps=eps,max_iter=100)\n",
    "    #print(eps,E_eps[i])    \n",
    "ieps = np.argmax(E_eps)\n",
    "print('The optimal value of eps:',eps_list[ieps])\n",
    "\n",
    "w_em = w_eps[ieps]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Hopfield approximation (HF)\n",
    "w_hf = EM.hopfield_method(seqs)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pseudo Likelihood Estimation (PLE)\n",
    "w_ple = EM.PLE_method(seqs)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We compare the performances of these methods."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7fd16f694a58>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 252x201.6 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nx,ny = 1,1\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(ny,nx,figsize=(nx*3.5,ny*2.8))\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot([-1,1],[-1,1])\n",
    "ax.plot(w_true,w_hf,'g^',marker='^',mfc='none',markersize=4,label='HF')\n",
    "ax.plot(w_true,w_ple,'bs',marker='s',mfc='none',markersize=4,label='PLE')\n",
    "ax.plot(w_true,w_em,'ro',marker='o',markersize=4,label='EM')\n",
    "ax.set_xlim([-0.6,0.6])\n",
    "ax.set_ylim([-0.6,0.6])       \n",
    "ax.set_xticks([-0.6,0,0.6])\n",
    "ax.set_yticks([-0.6,0,0.6])\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Actual interactions')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Inferred interactions')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<div>\n",
       "<style scoped>\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n",
       "        vertical-align: middle;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n",
       "        vertical-align: top;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe thead th {\n",
       "        text-align: right;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "</style>\n",
       "<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n",
       "  <thead>\n",
       "    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n",
       "      <th></th>\n",
       "      <th>Method</th>\n",
       "      <th>Mean squared error</th>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "  </thead>\n",
       "  <tbody>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>0</th>\n",
       "      <td>EM</td>\n",
       "      <td>0.000515</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>1</th>\n",
       "      <td>HF</td>\n",
       "      <td>0.002071</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>2</th>\n",
       "      <td>PLE</td>\n",

       "</table>\n",
       "</div>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "  Method  Mean squared error\n",
       "0     EM            0.000515\n",
       "1     HF            0.002071\n",
       "2    PLE            0.000494"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "MSE_em = ((w_true - w_em)**2).mean()\n",
    "MSE_hf = ((w_true - w_hf)**2).mean()\n",
    "MSE_ple = ((w_true - w_ple)**2).mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame([['EM',MSE_em],['HF',MSE_hf],['PLE',MSE_ple]],\n",
    "                  columns = ['Method','Mean squared error'])\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
